      "value": {
        "latex": "Déterminer la distance du point $A$ au plan $(P)$\n\n\\begin{enumerate}",
        "html": ""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c214ecf9-2596-444e-8fe0-ff7c671b75cb",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "La distance d'un point $A=(x_0,y_0,z_0)$ à un plan $P$ d'équation \n$ax+by+cz+d=0$ est donnée par la formule :\n$$d(A,P) = \\frac{|ax_0+by_0+cz_0+d|}{\\sqrt{a^2+b^2+c^2}}.$$\nOn trouve donc\n  \\begin{enumerate}",
        "html": ""
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "61a17feb-e0ae-4516-90bb-d2a180c0e45d",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$A(1,0,2)$ et $(P): 2x+y+z+4=0$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(A(1,0,2)\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\((P): 2x+y+z+4=0\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "2fb3852b-1572-49d8-9d9b-5935fd92324f",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "$d(A,P)=\\frac{|2\\cdot 1+1\\cdot 0+1\\cdot 2+4|}{\\sqrt{2^2+1^2+1^2}}= \\frac{8}{\\sqrt6}=\\frac{4\\sqrt6}{3}$.",
        "html": "<p><span class=\"math inline\">\\(d(A,P)=\\frac{|2\\cdot 1+1\\cdot 0+1\\cdot 2+4|}{\\sqrt{2^2+1^2+1^2}}= \\frac{8}{\\sqrt6}=\\frac{4\\sqrt6}{3}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
